<p>An illustration of when to prefer the first method to the second one is when you need to avoid overriding a function's previous definitions.</p>

<p>With</p>

<pre><code>if (condition){
    function myfunction(){
        // Some code
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>, this definition of <code>myfunction</code> will override any previous definition, since it will be done at parse-time.</p>

<p>While</p>

<pre><code>if (condition){
    var myfunction = function (){
        // Some code
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>does the correct job of defining <code>myfunction</code> only when <code>condition</code> is met.</p>
